-- Australian, N.Z. Stocks: Warehouse Group, Magma Metals
-- B y   B e n   S h a r p l e s
-- 2012-02-03T06:29:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-03/australian-n-z-stocks-warehouse-group-magma-metals.html
Australia ’s  S&P/ASX 200 Index 
declined 0.4 percent to 4,251.2 at the close of trading in
Sydney, falling 0.9 percent through the week. New Zealand’s NZX
50 Index was little changed at 3,312.23 in Wellington, having
retreated 0.5 percent this week.  The following were among the most active shares in the
market. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.  Magma Metals Ltd. (MMW)   surged 69 percent to 13.5
Australian cents after  Panoramic Resources Ltd. (PAN)  announced a
takeover bid for the company. Panoramic Resources shares slipped
0.8 percent to A$1.26.  Warehouse Group Ltd. (WHS)   slid 3.3 percent to NZ$2.95
after New Zealand’s biggest discount retailer cut its full-year
earnings forecast as much as 11 percent because of pressure on
profit margins.  To contact the reporter on this story:
